<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-31T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-31T06:00:00-05:00" n="100" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/7288: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Barcelona</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-31T11:00:00+00:00">January 31, 1938—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 3—9:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>870. An official statement places the number of deaths from yesterday’s
                            air raids at 150 as of last night. Unofficial estimates place them at
                            twice that figure.</p>
                        <p>The statement also asserts that the Government’s offer to desist from
                            raids in cities in the far rear guard, quoted in my 867, January 29, 10
                                a.m.,<note n="11" xml:id="d100fn11">Not printed.</note> has been
                            rejected by a speaker over the Salamanca radio.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>